File: Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is rubbishing claims made by the chair of the SA Medical Research Council, Glenda Gray. Gray, who serves on the Ministerial Advisory Committee on COVID-19, is reported to have said government is not listening to its advice She is quoted saying lockdown regulations are not based on science but thumb-sucked and that Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital is seeing malnutrition cases for the first time in decades. READ: Expect influx of COVID-19 patients: Mkhize Mkhize says Gray has made incorrect, unfounded statements and accuses her of unprofessional conduct. He points out there has been a decrease in the number of malnutrition cases as compared to the past 4 years. The minister also says the 'thumb suck' comments undermines the work done to fight the virus. -Â Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.